   <topic id="FAR_25_100"
          ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
          class="- topic/topic ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">25.100</ph> Scope of subpart.</title>
      <body class="- topic/body ">
         <ol id="d1593e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1615e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>This subpart implements-</p>
               <ol id="d1593e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1615e16" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. chapter 83</xref>,
Buy American;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1615e23" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        Executive Order 10582,
December 17, 1954;
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1615e28" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        Executive Order 13881,
July 15, 2019; and
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1615e33" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        Waiver of the domestic
content test of the Buy American statute for acquisition of commercially
available off-the-shelf (COTS) items in accordance with 41 U.S.C.
1907, but see <xref href="25.101.dita#FAR_25_101"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.101</xref>(a)(2)(ii).
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1615e41" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> It applies
to supplies acquired for use in the United States, including supplies
acquired under contracts set aside for small business concerns,
if-</p>
               <ol id="d1593e68" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1615e47" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The supply contract exceeds the
micro-purchase threshold; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1615e52" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The supply
portion of a contract for services that involves the furnishing
of supplies (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.</i>, lease) exceeds the micro-purchase threshold.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </body>
